</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="063E82AAE65D6CBFE6BD1D59E0CC3CE0" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="14CE1B4A453709889A97608E5DE46AAF" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="23A72D6180C5AEF5B0927942C3C59C5E" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
The species is known only from the type locality in Mt. Hon Ba at 200-400 m altitude. It is suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="4E32419B25BAB9728A8C7861AD4740EE" authorityName="Tagane &amp; V. S. Dang" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Aporosa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aporosa tetragona" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tetragona">
<emphasis id="C611AA5822D298BD97DC1CC931EBD0AB" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Aporosa tetragona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be placed under the IUCN category 'Critically 
<normalizedToken id="94E09AE8134AE5C57F90B6BB14BB97ED" originalValue="Endangered’">Endangered'</normalizedToken>
(CR) (
<bibRefCitation id="2FE9A8530E19489DA175A9FB5613F67A" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland / Cambridge" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 32" refId="B10" refString="IUCN, 2012. IUCN red list categories and criteria, version 3.1. IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland/Cambridge: 1 - 32" title="IUCN red list categories and criteria, version 3.1" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
) because of its limited distribution with an area of occupancy estimated to be less than 10 km2 (criterion B2 a) and a small number of individuals estimated to be less than 250. Recent botanical inventories carried out in this narrow area along stream discovered several new species, including 
<taxonomicName id="9456F6C96A31C1EA9B51D391803FD080" authorityName="Joongku Lee, T. B. Tran &amp; R. K. Choudhary" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Dilleniaceae" genus="Dillenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dillenia tetrapetala" order="Gunnerales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tetrapetala">
<emphasis id="AE09C6436CF4135E3603395AA9209FDA" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Dillenia tetrapetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Joongku Lee, T. B. Tran &amp; R. K. Choudhary (
<bibRefCitation id="BC7418D26F909F25C59D3B2ED6E91CC4" author="Choudhary, RK" journalOrPublisher="Annales Botanici Fennici" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" pagination="369 - 376" publicationUrl="10.5735/085.049.0608" refId="B3" refString="Choudhary, RK, Bach, TT, Nong, LV, Hai, DV, Quang, BH, Lee, YM, Park, SH, Lee, C, Lee, J, 2012. Dillenia tetrapetala (Dilleniaceae), a new species from Hon Ba Nature Reserve, Vietnam. Annales Botanici Fennici 49: 369 - 376, DOI: 10.5735/085.049.0608" title="Dillenia tetrapetala (Dilleniaceae), a new species from Hon Ba Nature Reserve, Vietnam." url="10.5735/085.049.0608" volume="49" year="2012">Choudhary et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="9002176B699E14CDFF05664E0068D708" authorityName="Tagane &amp; V.S.Dang" authorityYear="2015" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniothalamus flagellistylus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="flagellistylus">
<emphasis id="DFC2D5A92D545C15AF1164DF7E2C37E4" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Goniothalamus flagellistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Tagane &amp; V. S. Dang 
<pageBreakToken id="9BD8E4C7F01170ABED35ABD97316C33F" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" start="start">(</pageBreakToken>
<bibRefCitation id="07D8F75164C0C0FD2395AEB26DD58508" author="Tagane, S" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" pagination="1 - 8" publicationUrl="10.3897/phytokeys.50.4427" refId="B17" refString="Tagane, S, Dang, VS, Yahara, T, Toyama, H, Tran, H, 2015. Goniothalamus flagellistylus Tagane &amp; Dang VS (Annonaceae), a new species from Mt. Hon Ba, Vietnam. PhytoKeys 50: 1 - 8, DOI: 10.3897/phytokeys.50.4427" title="Goniothalamus flagellistylus Tagane &amp; Dang VS (Annonaceae), a new species from Mt. Hon Ba, Vietnam." url="10.3897/phytokeys.50.4427" volume="50" year="2015">Tagane et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="8E9398D0281F61D49449C629922572DC" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Vanilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vanilla atropogon" order="Microspermae" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="atropogon">
<emphasis id="EE32C537DEC9C55AFF61AB26E14DD0E4" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Vanilla atropogon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schuit., Aver. &amp; 
<normalizedToken id="15A711F03F805A69E41AE88B3A3BB632" originalValue="Rybková">Rybkova</normalizedToken>
(Schuiteman et al. 2012), all of which are rare and endemic to Mt. Hon Ba. Therefore further collection efforts around this area are necessary to accurately understand the flora there and to update the conservation status of the species.
</paragraph>
